{
  "text": "Since cohom Ban K (X, Y ) exists only for finite-dimensional X, Y \u2208 Ban K , the recognition theorem is essentially repeats the one in rigid setting. 3.3. Example: Geometric Satake correspondence. Let K be a spherically complete extension of Q p \u2282 K \u2282 Q p , G K be a smooth split semi-simple simply connected group scheme over K and\u01e6 K be the reductive group scheme corresponding to the dual root datum. The geometric Satake correspondence from [CITATION_1] 14.1] states that there is a monoidal equivalence of rigid abelian categories ",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "14127684"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "14127684": {
      "title": "Geometric Langlands duality and representations of algebraic groups over commutative rings",
      "abstract": "In this paper we give a geometric version of the Satake isomorphism. Given a connected complex reductive algebraic group, we show that the category of representations of its Langlands dual is naturally equivalent to a certain category of perverse sheaves on the complex affine Grassmannian. We can work with perverse sheaves with coefficients in an arbitrary commutative ring and then we recover the representation theory of the split form of the dual group over the commutative ring."
    }
  }
